Name truncated from gsmlgs_sheardisplacementstructure to gsmlgs_sheardispstructure to accommodate Oracle's 30 character identifier (table name) size limit.

PostGIS: All tables created WITH OIDS to allow editing in applications such as QuantumGIS. Oracle: This is a PostGIS model. Table and field names are exactly the same in the Oracle version, only the case of the names differs (upper case). Data types map as follows. - numeric(32,0) -> NUMBER(32,0); - text -> NVARCHAR2(1024). - geometry -> MDSYS.SDO_GEOMETRY
